verbose_text: The low bilirubin levels were found to be significantly associated to CAD whereas UGTA1A polymorphisms were not, with odds ratio of 0.9 (CI : 0.86-0.94, P = 2.6 x 10 -6) for men and 0.77 (CI : 0.68-0.87, P = 3.2 x 10 -5) for women respectively for each 0.1mg/dl increase in bilirubin levels [XREF_BIBR].
